                            <comment id="14681707" author="saifasif" created="Tue, 11 Aug 2015 12:13:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=britter&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;britter&quot;&gt;Benedikt Ritter&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Did you get a chance to look into this? I also made some unit tests for my newly added function. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible use cases :-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. We need to extract out certain phrases (that are quoted or are wrapped in some characters) from our file parsers that don&apos;t always work on regex. So instead of writing a method to skip these characters, we can simply unwrap from StringUtils.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Parsing a CSV file manually without using regex often results in quoted fields. Instead of wiring in the logic to skip wrapping characters in the parser itself, we can only focus on the parsing and then rely on StringUtils.unwrap to take care of the unwrapping for us.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
